Hayden Owens
Operating Systems Project 3 - README

W,A,S,D are used to move around the image without zooming

F will zoom out, R will zoom in

T will increase maxiter by a scalar, G will decrease maxiter by a scalar
    - This is useful for rapid increases or decreases

Y will increase maxiter by 10, H will decrease maxiter by 10
    - This is useful for finer adjustments when already zoomed in significantly

Left click will center the image at the click

Right click will center the image at the click and zoom in

1-8 will specify the number of threads to use
